properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 7 at 7:56PM EST until February 9 at 11:27AM EST by NWS Peachtree City GA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Georgia...

Oconee River near Penfield affecting Clarke...Greene and Oconee
Counties

Oconee River near Milledgeville affecting Baldwin...Washington and
Wilkinson Counties

Oconee River near Oconee affecting Johnson...Washington and
Wilkinson Counties


...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Georgia...
Oconee River near Oconee affecting Washington and Wilkinson
Counties

The Flood Warning continues for
The Oconee River near Milledgeville.
* Until Sunday morning.
* At 7 PM Friday the stage was 31.9 feet, and falling.
* Minor flooding is occurring is forecast to continue.
* Flood stage is 22 feet.
* The river will continue to fall to below flood stage by Sunday
morning.
* At 30 feet, Minor flooding continues to expand further into the
woodlands and pasture upstream and downstream from the gage near
the Georgia Highway 22 and 24 bridge. Fishing Creek backs up and
a few buildings along the creek will be flooded. Also Tanyard
Branch Stream between East Thomas and East Charleston Streets in
Milledgeville will flood. Sinclair Dam will likely have four to
five gates open to reach this height.
